'''Jack Hylton''' ([[July 2]], [[1892]]&ndash;[[January 29]], [[1965]]) was an [[England|English]] [[band leader]] and [[impresario]].

He was born in [[Great Lever]], [[Bolton|Bolton, Lancashire]]<!---in 1892 Bolton was then still part of Lancashire, its now part of Greater Manchester---> and died in [[Marylebone]], [[London]].

In 1965 a televised tribute to Hylton called ''The Stars Shine for Jack'' was held in London at the [[Theatre Royal, Drury Lane]].   It included many artists including [[Arthur Askey]], [[The Crazy Gang]], [[Marlene Dietrich]], [[Dickie Henderson]], and [[Shirley Bassey]].

